	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading mw-first-heading"><span class="mw-page-title-main">Scale (anatomy)</span></h1>
	<div id="bodyContent" class="vector-body">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"><span class="mw-redirectedfrom">(Redirected from <a href="/w/index.php?title=Scale_(zoology)&amp;redirect=no" class="mw-redirect" title="Scale (zoology)">Scale (zoology)</a>)</span></div>
		<div id="contentSub2"></div>
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#searchInput">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content mw-content-ltr" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Small rigid plate that grows out of an animal's skin</div>
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1033289096">.mw-parser-output .hatnote{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output div.hatnote{padding-left:1.6em;margin-bottom:0.5em}.mw-parser-output .hatnote i{font-style:normal}.mw-parser-output .hatnote+link+.hatnote{margin-top:-0.5em}</style><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Scale_(disambiguation)" class="mw-redirect mw-disambig" title="Scale (disambiguation)">Scale</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Keeled_scales_on_a_southern_watersnake_(26954310414).jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Keeled_scales_on_a_southern_watersnake_%2826954310414%29.jpg/250px-Keeled_scales_on_a_southern_watersnake_%2826954310414%29.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="167" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Keeled_scales_on_a_southern_watersnake_%2826954310414%29.jpg/375px-Keeled_scales_on_a_southern_watersnake_%2826954310414%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Keeled_scales_on_a_southern_watersnake_%2826954310414%29.jpg/500px-Keeled_scales_on_a_southern_watersnake_%2826954310414%29.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1440" data-file-height="960" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Keeled_scales_on_a_southern_watersnake_(26954310414).jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Keeled scales of a <a href="/wiki/Colubrid" class="mw-redirect" title="Colubrid">colubrid</a> snake (<a href="/wiki/Banded_water_snake" title="Banded water snake">banded water snake</a>; <i>Nerodia fasciata</i>)</div></div></div>
<p>In most <a href="/wiki/Biology" title="Biology">biological</a> <a href="/wiki/Nomenclature" title="Nomenclature">nomenclature</a>, a <b>scale</b> (<a href="/wiki/Ancient_Greek_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Ancient Greek language">Ancient Greek</a>: <span lang="grc"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%CE%BB%CE%B5%CF%80%CE%AF%CF%82" class="extiw" title="wikt:λεπίς">λεπίς</a></span>, <small><a href="/wiki/Romanization_of_Ancient_Greek" class="mw-redirect" title="Romanization of Ancient Greek">romanized</a>:&#160;</small><span title="Ancient Greek-language romanization"><i lang="grc-Latn">lepís</i></span>; <a href="/wiki/Latin_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Latin language">Latin</a>: <i lang="la"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/squama" class="extiw" title="wikt:squama">squāma</a></i>) is a small rigid <a href="/wiki/Plate_(animal_anatomy)" class="mw-redirect" title="Plate (animal anatomy)">plate</a> that grows out of an <a href="/wiki/Animal" title="Animal">animal</a>'s <a href="/wiki/Skin" title="Skin">skin</a> to provide protection. In <a href="/wiki/Lepidoptera" title="Lepidoptera">lepidopteran</a> (<a href="/wiki/Butterfly" title="Butterfly">butterfly</a> and <a href="/wiki/Moth" title="Moth">moth</a>) species, scales are plates on the surface of the <a href="/wiki/Insect_wing" title="Insect wing">insect wing</a>, and provide coloration. Scales are quite common and have evolved multiple times through <a href="/wiki/Convergent_evolution" title="Convergent evolution">convergent evolution</a>, with varying structure and function.
</p><p>Scales are generally classified as part of an organism's <a href="/wiki/Integumentary_system" title="Integumentary system">integumentary system</a>. There are various types of scales according to shape and to <a href="/wiki/Class_(biology)" title="Class (biology)">class</a> of animal.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
